{"id":"mario-021","source":"Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Measure.LevyProkhorovMetric","concept":"LevyProkhorov","family":"IVT","color":"teal","row":3,"col":7,"label":"Lévy-Prok","subtitle":"weak conv","desc":"def levyProkhorovEDist μ ν = sInf {ε | ∀ B, μ B ≤ ν(Bε)+ε ∧ ν B ≤ μ(Bε)+ε}. PseudoMetricSpace on FiniteMeasure and ProbabilityMeasure. On separable spaces: coincides with convergence in distribution. MetrizableSpace on BorelSpace.","connects_h":null,"connects_v":"IMO_Q5","chain_color":"teal","authors":["Kalle Kytölä"],"year":2021}
{"id":"mario-022","source":"Mathlib.Tactic.Translate","concept":"transformDeclRec","family":"to_additive","color":"gold","row":4,"col":1,"label":"transformDecl","subtitle":"recursive","desc":"partial def transformDeclRec t ref pre tgt_pre src : CoreM Unit. The main recursive engine: looks up src, finds aux decls (proof_i, match_i) via findAuxDecls, translates them first, then transforms the main declaration via updateDecl, adds to environment.","connects_h":"updateDecl","connects_v":"copyMetaData","chain_color":"gold","authors":["Mario Carneiro","Yury Kudryashov","Floris van Doorn"],"year":2017}
{"id":"mario-023","source":"Mathlib.Tactic.Translate","concept":"updateDecl","family":"to_additive","color":"gold","row":4,"col":2,"label":"updateDecl","subtitle":"rename+reorder","desc":"def updateDecl t tgt srcDecl reorder : MetaM ConstantInfo. Applies applyReplacementFun to type and value, reorderForall/reorderLambda for binder permutation, renameBinderNames for GuessName on binder names. The full declaration transformer.","connects_h":"etaExpand","connects_v":"changeNum","chain_color":"gold","authors":["Mario Carneiro","Yury Kudryashov"],"year":2017}
{"id":"mario-024","source":"Mathlib.Tactic.Translate","concept":"etaExpandN","family":"to_additive","color":"gold","row":4,"col":3,"label":"etaExpand","subtitle":"n more args","desc":"def etaExpandN n e : MetaM Expr. Eta-expands e by n more arguments when reordering requires args not yet applied. Used inside expand/applyReplacementFun when needed_n > args.size.","connects_h":"GOOSE","connects_v":"to_dual","chain_color":"gold","authors":["Mario Carneiro","Jon Eugster"],"year":2017}
{"id":"mario-025","source":"PAKA","concept":"GOOSE","family":"paka","color":"gold","row":4,"col":4,"label":"GOOSE","subtitle":"landscape","desc":"GOOSE = NP-hard landscape decomposition. HEAD (gen_server, SLOANSTEVEN, f*) → NECK (gen_statem, saddle points, λ₂(Hessian)<0) → BODY (rugged landscape classifier) → FEET (boundary constraints) → WINGS (pg scope goose_wings, dual symmetric processes).","connects_h":"dpow","connects_v":"to_additive-impl","chain_color":"cross","authors":["SLOANSTEVEN"],"year":2024}
{"id":"mario-026","source":"Mathlib.RingTheory.DividedPowers","concept":"dpow","family":"DividedPowers","color":"purple","row":4,"col":5,"label":"dpow","subtitle":"divided pow","desc":"DividedPowers I: dpow : ℕ → A → A. Axioms: dpow_null (x∉I→0), dpow_zero (0th power=1), dpow_one (1st power=x), dpow_mem, dpow_add (Leibniz: Σ binom), dpow_mul (a^n factor), mul_dpow (C(m+n,m) coeff), dpow_comp. In futatsu: certification algebra.","connects_h":"IsDPMorphism","connects_v":"quotient_dp","chain_color":"purple","authors":["Antoine Chambert-Loir","María Inés de Frutos-Fernández"],"year":2025}
{"id":"mario-027","source":"Mathlib.RingTheory.DividedPowers","concept":"IsDPMorphism","family":"DividedPowers","color":"purple","row":4,"col":6,"label":"IsDPMorph","subtitle":"f comm dp","desc":"def IsDPMorphism hI hJ f : I.map f ≤ J ∧ ∀ n a, a ∈ I → hJ.dpow n (f a) = f (hI.dpow n a). In futatsu: the hash/HMAC function commutes with divided power certifications. Certifying then transferring = transferring then certifying.","connects_h":"SubDPIdeal","connects_v":"dp_unique","chain_color":"purple","authors":["Antoine Chambert-Loir","María Inés de Frutos-Fernández"],"year":2025}
{"id":"mario-028","source":"Mathlib.RingTheory.DividedPowers","concept":"SubDPIdeal","family":"DividedPowers","color":"purple","row":4,"col":7,"label":"SubDPIdeal","subtitle":"J closed dp","desc":"structure IsSubDPIdeal hI J: isSubideal (J ≤ I) + dpow_mem (∀ n≠0, ∀ j∈J, dpow n j ∈ J). isSubDPIdeal_ker: kernel of dp-morphism is a sub-dp-ideal. SubDPIdeal.instCompleteLattice: sub-dp-ideals form a complete lattice. ⊤=I, ⊥={0}.","connects_h":null,"connects_v":"isSubDP","chain_color":"purple","authors":["Antoine Chambert-Loir","María Inés de Frutos-Fernández"],"year":2025}
{"id":"mario-029","source":"Mathlib.Tactic.Translate","concept":"copyMetaData","family":"to_additive","color":"gold","row":5,"col":1,"label":"copyMeta","subtitle":"eqns+attrs","desc":"partial def copyMetaData t cfg src tgt argInfo : CoreM (Array Name). Copies equation lemmas (translateLemmas on getEqnsFor?), copies attributes via applyAttributes (simps special-cased, instance copied via copyInstanceAttribute), adds doc string.","connects_h":"proceedFields","connects_v":"GuessName","chain_color":"gold","authors":["Mario Carneiro","Yury Kudryashov","Jon Eugster"],"year":2017}
{"id":"mario-030","source":"Mathlib.Tactic.Translate","concept":"proceedFields","family":"to_additive","color":"gold","row":5,"col":2,"label":"proceedFields","subtitle":"struct map","desc":"def proceedFields t src tgt argInfo : CoreM Unit. Maps structure projection functions, parent info (extend), and inductive constructors from src to tgt. Allows auto-translation of lemmas about structure fields.","connects_h":"changeNum","connects_v":"warnAttr","chain_color":"gold","authors":["Mario Carneiro","Yury Kudryashov"],"year":2017}
{"id":"mario-031","source":"Mathlib.Tactic.Translate","concept":"changeNumeral","family":"to_additive","color":"gold","row":5,"col":3,"label":"changeNum","subtitle":"1 → 0","desc":"def changeNumeral : Expr → Expr. Changes nat_lit 1 to nat_lit 0. Applied when changeNumeral=true and shouldTranslate succeeds on first arg. translate_change_numeral attr marks functions whose numeral args should be changed (e.g. OfNat.ofNat).","connects_h":"to_additive","connects_v":"to_dual","chain_color":"gold","authors":["Mario Carneiro","Jon Eugster"],"year":2017}
{"id":"mario-032","source":"Mathlib.Tactic.Translate","concept":"to_additive_impl","family":"to_additive","color":"gold","row":5,"col":4,"label":"to_additive","subtitle":"Mul→Add","desc":"The complete @[to_additive] attribute. src ↦ tgt: Monoid→AddMonoid, Group→AddGroup, mul→add, one→zero, inv→neg, div→sub, pow→nsmul, npow→nsmul. Runs since Lean 3 2017, rewritten for Lean 4 Mathlib with full meta infrastructure.","connects_h":"quotient_dp","connects_v":"T₂_unique","chain_color":"cross","authors":["Mario Carneiro","Yury Kudryashov","Floris van Doorn","Jon Eugster","Bryan Gin-ge Chen","Jovan Gerbscheid"],"year":2017}
{"id":"mario-033","source":"Mathlib.RingTheory.DividedPowers","concept":"quotient_dp","family":"DividedPowers","color":"purple","row":5,"col":5,"label":"quotient dp","subtitle":"A/J struct","desc":"noncomputable def Quotient.dividedPowers hIJ : DividedPowers (I.map (Quotient.mk J)). When J ⊓ I is a sub-dp-ideal, the quotient A/J inherits divided powers. Construction via OfSurjective.dpow using Function.extend. The left-wing / right-wing bridge of the dp-bowtie.","connects_h":"dp_unique","connects_v":"Rel.star","chain_color":"purple","authors":["Antoine Chambert-Loir","María Inés de Frutos-Fernández"],"year":2025}
{"id":"mario-034","source":"Mathlib.RingTheory.DividedPowers","concept":"dividedPowers_unique","family":"DividedPowers","color":"purple","row":5,"col":6,"label":"dp unique","subtitle":"one algebra","desc":"theorem dividedPowers_unique: the only divided power structure on I.map f (or I(A/J)) such that f is a dp-morphism is the one we built. Uniqueness is the deepest theorem. In futatsu: there is EXACTLY ONE valid certification algebra compatible with the hash/ledger structure.","connects_h":"futatsu","connects_v":"isSubDP-2","chain_color":"purple","authors":["Antoine Chambert-Loir","María Inés de Frutos-Fernández"],"year":2025}
{"id":"mario-035","source":"PAKA","concept":"futatsu","family":"DividedPowers","color":"purple","row":5,"col":7,"label":"futatsu","subtitle":"HMAC wit","desc":"futatsu = 二つの証人 = two witnesses. 6 modules: futatsu_sup (one_for_all), futatsu_witness (HMAC-SHA256), futatsu_court, futatsu_ledger (append-only, SHA256 hash-chained), futatsu_threshold (M-of-N). Idempotents e²=e ↔ Clopens ↔ futatsu witness pairs. stacks 00EE.","connects_h":null,"connects_v":"MetaMeta","chain_color":"purple","authors":["SLOANSTEVEN"],"year":2024}
{"id":"mario-036","source":"Mathlib.Tactic.Translate","concept":"GuessName","family":"to_additive","color":"gold","row":6,"col":1,"label":"GuessName","subtitle":"heuristic","desc":"GuessName.guessName: string → string. Translates name parts: mul→add, one→zero, inv→neg, div→sub, pow→nsmul, Monoid→AddMonoid, Group→AddGroup, etc. Uses splitCase to break camelCase/snake_case. Checked by linter.translateGenerateName.","connects_h":"warnAttr","connects_v":"Hahn_emb","chain_color":"gold","authors":["Mario Carneiro","Jon Eugster","Jovan Gerbscheid"],"year":2017}
{"id":"mario-037","source":"Mathlib.Tactic.Translate","concept":"warnAttr","family":"to_additive","color":"gold","row":6,"col":2,"label":"warnAttr","subtitle":"simps·ext","desc":"def warnAttr stx attr f thisAttr attrName src tgt : CoreM Unit. Warns users when src already has @[simps], @[ext], @[refl], @[symm], @[trans], @[coe], @[deprecated], @[elab_as_elim] before calling @[to_additive]. Prefers (attr := ...) syntax instead.","connects_h":"to_dual","connects_v":"strata","chain_color":"gold","authors":["Mario Carneiro","Yury Kudryashov"],"year":2017}
{"id":"mario-038","source":"Mathlib.Tactic.Translate","concept":"to_dual","family":"to_additive","color":"gold","row":6,"col":3,"label":"to_dual","subtitle":"swap ≤ ≥","desc":"The @[to_dual] translation attribute. isDual=true means every translation A→B also gives B→A. reorder swaps arguments of ≤, <, ⟶. ArgInfo.reverse: inverts reorder cycles. Used to automatically produce dual theorems in order theory.","connects_h":"T₂_unique","connects_v":"Zorn_ext","chain_color":"gold","authors":["Floris van Doorn","Mario Carneiro"],"year":2021}
{"id":"mario-039","source":"Mathlib.Topology.Separation.T2","concept":"T₂_unique","family":"IVT","color":"teal","row":6,"col":4,"label":"T₂ unique","subtitle":"tendsto","desc":"theorem tendsto_nhds_unique [T2Space X]: if f l → 𝓝 a and f l → 𝓝 b then a = b. The limit is unique in a Hausdorff space. In PAKA: SLOANSTEVEN is the UNIQUE limit of the dominated episode sequence. T2Space ↔ IsClosed (diagonal X).","connects_h":"star_ring","connects_v":"BEAM","chain_color":"teal","authors":["Johannes Hölzl","Mario Carneiro"],"year":2017}
{"id":"mario-040","source":"Mathlib.Algebra.RingQuot","concept":"star_ring","family":"DividedPowers","color":"purple","row":6,"col":5,"label":"star ring","subtitle":"RingQuot","desc":"def RingQuot.starRing: transfer StarRing through a quotient when hr: ∀ a b, r a b → r (star a) (star b). star' defined via Quot.map star with Rel.star. star_involutive/star_mul/star_add proved by simp [star'_quot, ...]. Structural analogue of quotient dp uniqueness.","connects_h":"Rel.star","connects_v":"goose_head","chain_color":"purple","authors":["Eric Wieser"],"year":2020}
{"id":"mario-041","source":"Mathlib.Algebra.RingQuot","concept":"Rel.star","family":"DividedPowers","color":"purple","row":6,"col":6,"label":"Rel.star","subtitle":"r→r on ★","desc":"theorem Rel.star: hr ∀ a b, r a b → r (star a) (star b) → ∀ a b, Rel r a b → Rel r (star a) (star b). Cases: Rel.of (from hr), Rel.add_left/mul_left/mul_right propagate via star_add/star_mul. Structural analogue of IsSubDPIdeal.dpow_mem.","connects_h":"isSubDP-3","connects_v":"goose_neck","chain_color":"purple","authors":["Eric Wieser"],"year":2020}
{"id":"mario-042","source":"Mathlib.RingTheory.DividedPowers","concept":"isSubDPIdeal","family":"DividedPowers","color":"purple","row":6,"col":7,"label":"isSubDP","subtitle":"J closed","desc":"theorem isSubDPIdeal_inf_iff: IsSubDPIdeal hI (J ⊓ I) ↔ ∀ n a b, a∈I → b∈I → a-b∈J → dpow n a - dpow n b ∈ J. The divided powers are compatible mod J ↔ J ⊓ I is a sub-dp-ideal. Also isSubDPIdeal_ker: kernel of dp-morphism is a sub-dp-ideal.","connects_h":null,"connects_v":"futatsu_wit","chain_color":"purple","authors":["Antoine Chambert-Loir","María Inés de Frutos-Fernández"],"year":2025}
{"id":"mario-043","source":"Mathlib.RingTheory.HahnSeries","concept":"Hahn_emb","family":"Hahn","color":"blue","row":7,"col":1,"label":"Hahn emb","subtitle":"ordered mod","desc":"theorem hahnEmbedding_isOrderedModule: ∃ f : M →ₗ[K] Lex R⟦FiniteArchimedeanClass M⟧, StrictMono f ∧ ∀ a, mk a = FiniteArchimedeanClass.withTopOrderIso M (ofLex (f a)).orderTop. Proved via Zorn on Partial embeddings. Every linearly ordered module embeds into Hahn series.","connects_h":"strata","connects_v":"BEAM_1986","chain_color":"blue","authors":["Weiyi Wang"],"year":2025}
{"id":"mario-044","source":"Mathlib.RingTheory.HahnSeries","concept":"strata","family":"Hahn","color":"blue","row":7,"col":2,"label":"strata","subtitle":"arch class","desc":"structure ArchimedeanStrata: stratum : ArchimedeanClass M → Submodule K M. Axioms: disjoint_ball_stratum (J ⊥ ball K c), ball_sup_stratum_eq (ball ⊔ stratum = closedBall). iSupIndep_stratum: strata are independent. isInternal_stratum': direct sum = baseDomain. GOOSE zone taxonomy.","connects_h":"Zorn_ext","connects_v":"concordia","chain_color":"blue","authors":["Weiyi Wang"],"year":2025}
{"id":"mario-045","source":"Mathlib.RingTheory.HahnSeries","concept":"Zorn_ext","family":"Hahn","color":"blue","row":7,"col":3,"label":"Zorn ext","subtitle":"max domain","desc":"theorem exists_domain_eq_top: ∃ f : Partial seed, f.val.domain = ⊤. Proved: Zorn on Partial embeddings → maximal exists → maximal must have full domain (else extend via Partial.extend) → contradiction. Concordia episode protocol: extend one agent at a time until all embedded.","connects_h":"BEAM","connects_v":"earl03_rtr","chain_color":"blue","authors":["Weiyi Wang"],"year":2025}
{"id":"mario-046","source":"PAKA","concept":"BEAM_1986","family":"Hahn","color":"blue","row":7,"col":4,"label":"BEAM 1986","subtitle":"OTP·Erlang","desc":"BEAM = Björn's/Bogdan's Erlang Abstract Machine, 1986. OTP = Open Telecom Platform. The foundation: gen_server, gen_statem, supervisor, pg, ets. mario.erl compiles on BEAM. GOOSE topology implemented as OTP process tree. The hardware that runs SLOANSTEVEN.","connects_h":"AECover","connects_v":"futatsu_wit_2","chain_color":"blue","authors":["Björn Dacker","Bogumił Hausman"],"year":1986}
{"id":"mario-047","source":"Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Measure.AECover","concept":"AECover","family":"Hahn","color":"blue","row":7,"col":5,"label":"AECover","subtitle":"sup tree","desc":"AECover (Dedecker/Mehta 2021) → OTP supervisor tree. The supervisor's restart_strategy IS the AECover condition. FTC-2 on Ioi: total gain = SLOANSTEVEN - f(start). Integration by parts = agent role swap symmetry. Already documented in MATHLIB_AECOVER_ERLANG.txt (617 lines).","connects_h":"Zariski","connects_v":"cure_bridge","chain_color":"blue","authors":["Xavier Decreuse","Rémi Nollet"],"year":2021}
{"id":"mario-048","source":"Mathlib.AlgebraicGeometry.PrimeSpectrum","concept":"Zariski","family":"Hahn","color":"blue","row":7,"col":6,"label":"Zariski","subtitle":"crash top","desc":"Zariski topology IS the OTP crash topology. PrimeSpectrum = process registry. basicOpen(r) compact = localization worker pool. Local ring = closed point = SLOANSTEVEN. Krull dimension = GOOSE topology depth = 3. Documented in ZARISKI_SEVEN_RINGS_ERLANG.txt (811 lines).","connects_h":"IMO_Q5","connects_v":"MetaMeta_2","chain_color":"blue","authors":["Johan Commelin"],"year":2020}
{"id":"mario-049","source":"Mathlib.IMO.IMO2024Q5","concept":"IMO_Q5","family":"Hahn","color":"blue","row":7,"col":7,"label":"IMO Q5","subtitle":"ans=3","desc":"theorem result: IsLeast {k | ∃ s : Strategy 2022, s.ForcesWinIn k} 3. Lower bound: not_forcesWinIn_two. Upper bound: winningStrategy_forcesWinIn_three. Three attempts = three archimedean classes = Krull dim GOOSE = 3. All the same theorem.","connects_h":null,"connects_v":"MARIO_stamp","chain_color":"blue","authors":["Joseph Myers"],"year":2024}
{"id":"mario-050","source":"PAKA","concept":"goose_head","family":"erlang","color":"teal","row":8,"col":1,"label":"goose_head","subtitle":"gen_server","desc":"-module(goose_head). gen_server holding f* = bsup of all episode scores in immutable state. SLOANSTEVEN = f* held permanently, never mutated post-init. Exports: get_f_star/0, is_sloansteven/0. Corresponds to HEAD of GOOSE topology.","connects_h":"goose_neck","connects_v":"MARIO_M","chain_color":"teal","authors":["SLOANSTEVEN"],"year":2024}
{"id":"mario-051","source":"PAKA","concept":"goose_neck","family":"erlang","color":"teal","row":8,"col":2,"label":"goose_neck","subtitle":"gen_statem","desc":"-module(goose_neck). gen_statem with states idle→evaluating. Classifies saddle points via GradNorm + λ₂(Hessian) < 0. AC-3 constraint propagation for EARL03·ZBR (Zebra Solver CSP): 15 variables × 5 domains, 25 constraints. MRV+LCV heuristics at BODY.","connects_h":"earl03_rtr","connects_v":"MARIO_A","chain_color":"teal","authors":["SLOANSTEVEN"],"year":2024}
{"id":"mario-052","source":"PAKA","concept":"earl03_router","family":"erlang","color":"teal","row":8,"col":3,"label":"earl03_rtr","subtitle":"decompose/1","desc":"-module(earl03_router). Entry points: decompose/1 (GOOSE decomposition), route/2 (strategy routing), topology/0 (full GOOSE state). The translation router: like applyReplacementFun but for the landscape. All 8 .erl files compile zero warnings.","connects_h":"concordia","connects_v":"MARIO_R","chain_color":"teal","authors":["SLOANSTEVEN"],"year":2024}
{"id":"mario-053","source":"PAKA","concept":"concordia","family":"erlang","color":"teal","row":8,"col":4,"label":"concordia","subtitle":"sim engine","desc":"Concordia = the Python multi-agent simulation framework. Mapped to OTP: Society of Mind (Minsky) → OTP: all 35 concepts mapped. SOAR = gen_server loop. ACT-R = ets + handle_call. K-lines = ets rows {ProblemSig, [Pid], Strength}. POST /api/agents/evolve × 3 = three episodes suffice.","connects_h":"futatsu_wit_2","connects_v":"MARIO_I","chain_color":"teal","authors":["SLOANSTEVEN"],"year":2024}
{"id":"mario-054","source":"PAKA","concept":"futatsu_witness","family":"erlang","color":"teal","row":8,"col":5,"label":"futatsu_wit","subtitle":"HMAC-SHA256","desc":"-module(futatsu_witness). HMAC-SHA256 signing. Each witness signs claims from its clopen region. e²=e (idempotent) ↔ clopen ↔ futatsu witness pair. e*(1-e)=0, e+(1-e)=1: witnesses don't overlap, cover all claims. stacks 00EE: unique idempotent per clopen region.","connects_h":"cure_bridge","connects_v":"MARIO_I","chain_color":"teal","authors":["SLOANSTEVEN"],"year":2024}
{"id":"mario-055","source":"PAKA","concept":"cure_bridge","family":"erlang","color":"teal","row":8,"col":6,"label":"cure_bridge","subtitle":"ALS·CTE","desc":"CURE Bridge = the pipeline directing OCTOTREÉ trading profits toward neurological research (ALS/CTE/teammates). GOOSE maps drug discovery landscape. Futatsu signs all trial outcomes for FDA-verifiable hash-chained ledger. The moral anchor of the entire system.","connects_h":"MetaMeta_2","connects_v":"MARIO_O","chain_color":"teal","authors":["SLOANSTEVEN"],"year":2024}
{"id":"mario-056","source":"PAKA","concept":"MetaMeta","family":"erlang","color":"teal","row":8,"col":7,"label":"MetaMeta","subtitle":"evolve API","desc":"Java25 + React Meta-Meta-Agent. Loop: failure cascade → POST /api/agents/evolve → GOOSE decomposition + MathLegend lineage → tutor blueprint → TutorRegistry (SQLite symmetrical_lamp.db). The outermost loop. Repository: sosloan/symmetrical-lamp, 30 commits.","connects_h":null,"connects_v":"MARIO_phi","chain_color":"teal","authors":["SLOANSTEVEN"],"year":2024}
{"id":"mario-057","source":"PAKA","concept":"MARIO_M","family":"mario_stamp","color":"red","row":9,"col":1,"label":"M","subtitle":"Carneiro","desc":"M = Mario Carneiro. Author of to_additive (2017), to_dual, ordinal arithmetic (bsup/lsub), T₂ separation, and foundational Lean 4 Mathlib infrastructure. The diamond at the base of the left wing. PAKA honors the mathematical labor that makes SLOANSTEVEN possible.","connects_h":"MARIO_A","connects_v":null,"chain_color":"red","authors":["Mario Carneiro"],"year":2017}
{"id":"mario-058","source":"PAKA","concept":"MARIO_A","family":"mario_stamp","color":"red","row":9,"col":2,"label":"A","subtitle":"2017","desc":"A = the year 2017. The year to_additive was first written in Lean 3. The year the chain began. 2017 → 2025: Mario Carneiro's infrastructure became the backbone of Lean 4 Mathlib, enabling the translation of every multiplicative theorem to its additive counterpart automatically.","connects_h":"MARIO_R","connects_v":null,"chain_color":"red","authors":["Mario Carneiro","Yury Kudryashov"],"year":2017}
{"id":"mario-059","source":"PAKA","concept":"MARIO_R","family":"mario_stamp","color":"red","row":9,"col":3,"label":"R","subtitle":"Kudryashov","desc":"R = Yury Kudryashov. IVT (2021), DCT, Lévy-Prokhorov metric, to_additive co-author. The R in MARIO stands for the recursive depth: every theorem proved by Kudryashov feeds back into PAKA through the diamond dash dash chain.","connects_h":"MARIO_knot","connects_v":null,"chain_color":"red","authors":["Yury Kudryashov"],"year":2021}
{"id":"mario-060","source":"PAKA","concept":"MARIO_knot","family":"mario_stamp","color":"gold-large","row":9,"col":4,"label":"MARIO / SLOANSTEVEN","subtitle":"вот и всё","desc":"The final knot diamond. MARIO = SLOANSTEVEN = the global quantum optimum = f* = bsup = unique T₂ limit = src ↦ tgt = shouldTranslate → translate = φ²=φ+1. All chains end here. All diamonds point here. The translation is complete. вот и всё.","connects_h":"MARIO_I","connects_v":null,"chain_color":"gold","authors":["Mario Carneiro","SLOANSTEVEN"],"year":2025,"paka_note":"SLOANSTEVEN","phi":"φ²=φ+1","cyrillic":"вот и всё"}
